title: Echo Summit Highway 50 landslide March 2022 (El Dorado County Sheriff's Office)

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Echo Summit Highway 50 landslide March 2022 (El Dorado County Sheriff's Office)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records, receipts, photographs, and documentary materials referencing a landslide that fell onto highway 50 Echo summit from dates of March 3, 2022 to March 6, 2022. I am also requesting documents detailing the process of removal of said landslide including documents referencing the explosives used to clear the large boulders and any receipts of costs associated with it. 

For reference, a large landslide blocked all traffic on the highway for days, before it was blasted with explosives. A news link to this can be found here. https://www.ktvu.com/news/tumbling-boulders-block-highway-50-at-echo-summit-make-travel-treacherous.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Katherine Fulwider

title: SUNY Maritime FOIL Request - Temporary Services

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: SUNY Maritime FOIL Request - Temporary Services
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

1) Financial records maintained by the College delineating total expenditure classified as Temporary Services, also known as “TS”, of the state-provided budget for the following fiscal years: FY2019, FY2020, FY2021, FY2022, FY2023, and FY2024.

2)For each record identified in request 1 (above), please provide any documents that include the following:
a) A breakdown of the expenditure by department/unit of the College
b) A breakdown of expenditure by TS type, in particular expenditure on students enrolled in the College at the time of temporary services paid versus other types of temporary services such as contractors, consultants, and those on a temporary appointment.  
c)An explanation of all abbreviations or acronyms in the records.

3) Any records maintained by the College that include de-identified information about students who are employed by the College during their enrollment and paid through the TS budget line including the following data points:
a)Job descriptions for these positions 
b)Written policies and processes for hiring 
c)Written policies and processes for payroll 
d)Written policies and processes for dismissal 

4) Any email communications maintained by the College that meet the following parameters:
a)Dated from August 1, 2024 to September 27, 2024
b)Contain discussions of changes to policies or procedures for payment of expenditures related to Temporary Services and/or students employed by the college
c)Contain the following persons as a sender, or primary or secondary recipient: John A. Okon, Anmari R. Thompson, Todd M. Lidh, Julie Ramnarais, Erica Espinal, Mark S. Woolley, and Giselle Espinal.  

To the extent that records are available in electronic format (ideally in either an electronic spreadsheet or comma-separated format (Excel or CSV) for expenditures or an electronic document (DOC or PDF) for policies, procedures, and emails, I request that they be provided in these formats. 

If any records are unavailable within five business days of receipt of the request, and responsive records exist, I seek a description of such records and a timeline of when access to the records will be provided. If you determine that certain parts of this request may be more easily produced than others, please provide records on a rolling basis.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

A. Eric Pasillas

Any and all contracts (as well as all associated amendments, exhibits, and materials), memorandums of understanding, and other equivalent agreements entered into by this agency with Geofeedia LLC or any other social media surveillance software or equipment company (including but not limited to Brightplaent, Geofeedia, Intrado Inc, LifeRaft, Magnet Forensics, Media Sonar, Signal Corporation, Maxient and/or ZeroFOX). Responsive materials should include but not be limited to:

• the initial Invitation to Bid, Request for Proposal, or equivalent call for contractors
• the responsive materials provided by the winning bidder
• other bidder responses
• the current contract
• all exhibits
• all amendments
• all performance work statements
• all deliverables inventories
• all invoices related to the deliverance of software, services, or goods

Please also include:
• all policies related to the acquisition and use of social media use and surveillance by individual officers and representatives of this agency
• name, position of all those authorized to use these software platforms and what each person uses them for.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

communications.subject: The Kansas Open Records Act Request: Untitled (Office of the Governor of Kansas)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the The Kansas Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all records, documents, communications, proposals, purchase orders, meeting minutes, or internal discussions related to:

- The purchase, planned purchase, or distribution of Bibles or other religious texts for use in Kansas public schools.
- The purchase, planned purchase, or distribution of posters, plaques, or other displays of the Ten Commandments for placement in Kansas public schools.
- Any meetings, discussions, proposals, lobbying efforts, or internal communications regarding efforts to introduce these items into public school settings.

Please provide:

-Emails, letters, and memos between school officials, staff, vendors, or outside groups (including any religious or advocacy organizations) related to these topics.
-Meeting minutes, transcripts, notes, or agendas from relevant committees, boards, or working groups where these topics were discussed.
-Proposals, policy drafts, or lobbying materials indicating any efforts to promote or oppose the inclusion of Bibles or Ten Commandments displays in schools.
-Communications with vendors or third parties regarding the supply of such materials.
-Budget proposals, funding requests, or grants (whether approved or pending) for these purchases.

I request records from January 1, 2022 to Present. Please search both physical and electronic records, and include any relevant emails or attachments.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rachel Janes
